{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc9b115d8-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s53"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"53"},"text":"§ 53.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Powers devolved on Secretary of the Interior on turning over of papers to States","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In all cases where, as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s54"},"text":"section 54 of this title","children":[],"tail":", the field notes, maps, records, and other papers appertaining to land titles in any State are turned over to the authorities of such State, the same authority, powers, and duties in relation to the survey, resurvey, or subdivision of the lands therein, and all matters and things connected therewith, as previously exercised by the surveyor general, whose district included such State, shall be vested in, and devolved upon, the Secretary of the Interior or such officer as he may designate."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc9b115d9-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"(R.S. § 2219; 1946 Reorg. Plan No. 3, § 403, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1946-07-16"},"text":"July 16, 1946","children":[],"tail":", 11 F.R. 7876, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/1100"},"text":"60 Stat. 1100","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc9b115da-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc9b115db-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idc9b115dc-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"R.S. § 2219 derived from ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1853-01-22/ch24/s1"},"text":"act Jan. 22, 1853, ch. 24, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/10/152"},"text":"10 Stat. 152","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idc9b115dd-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idc9b115de-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Surveyor General","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Abolition of office of surveyor general, see note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s51"},"text":"section 51 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idc9b115df-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"idc9b115e0-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions of other officers, employees, and agencies of Department of the Interior, with certain exceptions, to Secretary of the Interior, with power to delegate, see Reorg. Plan No. 3 of 1950, §§ 1, 2, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1950","children":[],"tail":", 15 F.R. 3174, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1262"},"text":"64 Stat. 1262","children":[],"tail":", set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1451"},"text":"section 1451 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Secretary of the Interior or such officer as he may designate” substituted for “Commissioner of the General Land Office” on authority of section 403 of Reorg. Plan No. 3 of 1946. See note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
